 Okay, so:  What I have is a view controller that has a UIScrollView and 2 sub views which can be scrolled between.  One subview has a video in it.  I have a variable in my main view controller called "Page" which stores what page is scrolled to at the moment, either 0 or 1 (for subview 1 or 2).

I'm trying to use protocol and delegate to carry this variable "page" to the sub view such that I can pause the video on sub view 1 if page = 1, but play it if page = 0.  

My code is:

VIEW CONTROLLER:

import UIKit 
import AVFoundation
protocol DataSentDelegate 
{ 
func scrollViewDidScroll(data: CGFloat) 
}

class VideosViewController: UIViewController, UIScrollViewDelegate {

var delegate:DataSentDelegate?

@IBOutlet weak var videosScrollView: UIScrollView!

override func viewDidLoad() 
{
    super.viewDidLoad()
    videosScrollView.delegate = self
}

func scrollViewDidScroll(_ scrollView: UIScrollView) 
{ 
let width = scrollView.frame.size.width 
let page = scrollView.contentOffset.x / width

 // If whole number
    if page.truncatingRemainder(dividingBy: 1) == 0
    {
    // Print page number
    print("Page: \(page)")
    }
    // Pass required data to delegate
    delegate?.scrollViewDidScroll(data: page)
}


SUB VIEW (XIB FILE)
